{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e88ca2f3-b06d-4383-baa1-7ab43944b0c4","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Register your package on NuGet.org\n\n- Go to **NuGet.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishing**\n- Add a **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher, specifying your **repo owner**, **repo name**, **workflow filename**, and optionally an **environment**\n\n### 2. Update your workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n**After (OIDC):**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n\nsteps:\n  - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n  # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n  - name: Install .NET 9+ SDK  # trusted publishing needs dotnet 9+\n    uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n    with:\n      dotnet-version: '9.x'\n\n  - name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n    run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes summary\n\n| Area | What to change |\n|---|---|\n| **NuGet.org** | Register a trusted publisher for your repo/workflow |\n| **`permissions`** | Add `id-token: write` to the job |\n| **`dotnet` version** | Use .NET SDK **9.0.200+** (built-in OIDC support) |\n| **`dotnet nuget push`** | **Remove** the `-k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` flag |\n| **Secret** | You can delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from repo settings once verified |\n\nThe .NET SDK automatically requests a short-lived OIDC token from GitHub and exchanges it with NuGet.org — no stored secret needed. Using a dedicated GitHub **environment** (e.g., `nuget-publish`) for the job is recommended for an extra trust boundary.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ba12d75-f58d-43f2-bc0f-61f0e6c9e692","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no existing workflow file to look at. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":606,"requestId":"4BCA:20A2EF:5DCDEA7:6910FF5:69EC0F43"},"id":"93014aa4-c776-412e-9453-01616a729499","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:17.852Z","parentId":"00aa4aff-9edf-461d-9393-81cff92685d3"}
